Module com.tuitionmanager.project3
Package com.tuitionmanager.project3

Class Student

java.lang.Object
com.tuitionmanager.project3.Student
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Student>
Direct Known Subclasses:
NonResident, Resident
public abstract class Student extends Object implements Comparable<Student>
This is a class that creates a Student object given an associated Profile object, Major enum, and total credits completed.

This class uses the Profile class and Major enum to store information about a student's profile and their academic records.

Author:
Aryan Patel

    • getClassStanding

      public String getClassStanding()
      This method gets a student object's class standing (FRESHMAN, SOPHOMORE, JUNIOR, SENIOR) based on the number of credits they have completed. The class standing is determined these conditions:

      Freshman, if credit completed is less than 30. Sophomore, if credit completed is greater or equal to 30 and less than 60. Junior, if credit completed is greater or equal to 60 and less than 90. Senior, if credit completed is greater or equal to 90.

      Returns:
      String which contains the student's class standing (FRESHMAN, SOPHOMORE, JUNIOR, SENIOR).

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object o)
      This method determines if a Student object is equal to another given Object.

      The process of checking equality involves first checking if the given Object is the Student object itself. If not, it then checks if the given object is an instance of the Student Class before it checks the equality of the Profile, Major enum, and creditCompleted values between the two objects.

      Note: This method uses the Profile class' equals() method to compare two Student objects because the Profile object attribute is used to compare two Student objects.

      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      o - Object input that is to be checked if it is equal to another Student object
      Returns:
      boolean which refers to whether the given Object is equal to another Student object

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Student studentCompare)
      This method compares a Student object with another Student object.

      This method uses the Profile class' compareTo() method to compare the two Profile objects between the two Student objects.

      The order of comparison is as follows: lname, fname, dob. This is because we are comparing only the Profiles associated with both Student objects. The method returns an int value which represents the relative position (BEFORE, AFTER, SAME), of one Student object to the other. Details can be found in the Profile class compareTo() method.

      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Student>
      Parameters:
      studentCompare - Student object input that is to be compared
      Returns:
      int which contains a value representing the relative order.

    • toString

      public String toString()
      This method returns the Student object as a String containing the student's Profile, Major, and credits completed.

      Note: This method uses the Profile and Major class' toString() method to display the Profile object representing the student's information and the Major enum representing the student's major. The method also utilizes the getClassStanding() method to display the student's class standing along with their credits completed.

      Overrides:
      toString in class Object
      Returns:
      String which represents a Student object
